Package org.opensextant.giscore.input.kml

Class KmlReader

java.lang.Object
org.opensextant.giscore.input.kml.KmlBaseReader
org.opensextant.giscore.input.kml.KmlReader
All Implemented Interfaces:
Closeable, AutoCloseable, IGISInputStream, IKml
public class KmlReader extends KmlBaseReader implements IGISInputStream
Wrapper to KmlInputStream that handles various house cleaning of parsing KML and KMZ sources. Caller does not need to know if target is KML or KMZ resource.

Handles the following tasks:

  • read from KMZ/KML files or URLs transparently
  • re-writing of URLs inside KMZ files to resolve relative URLs
  • rewrites relative URLs of NetworkLinks, inline or shared IconStyles, and Screen/GroundOverlays with respect to parent URL. Use UrlRef to get InputStream of links and resolve URI to original URL.
  • recursively read all features from referenced NetworkLinks
Author:
Jason Mathews, MITRE Corp. Created: Mar 5, 2009 9:12:19 AM

    • KmlReader

      public KmlReader(InputStream is, boolean isCompressed, URL baseUrl, Proxy proxy) throws IOException
      Create KmlReader using provided InputStream.
      Parameters:
      is - input stream for the kml content, never null
      isCompressed - True if the input stream is a compressed stream (e.g. KMZ resource) in which case relative links are resolved with respect to the baseUrl as KMZ "ZIP" entries as opposed to using the baseUrl as the parent URL context only.
      baseUrl - the base URL context from which relative links are resolved
      proxy - the Proxy through which URL connections will be made. If direct connection is desired, null should be specified.
      Throws:
      IOException - if an I/O error occurs

    • KmlReader

      public KmlReader(InputStream is, URL baseUrl, Proxy proxy) throws IOException
      Create KmlReader using provided InputStream. Automatically determines if source is KMZ or KML stream by checking the content.
      Parameters:
      is - input stream for the kml/kmz content, never null
      baseUrl - the base URL context from which relative links are resolved. If null then reader will not be able to resolve relative links.
      proxy - the Proxy through which URL connections will be made. If direct connection is desired, null should be specified.
      Throws:
      IOException - if an I/O error occurs

    • setMaxLinkCount

      public void setMaxLinkCount(int maxLinkCount)
      Set maximum number of NetworkLinks that are allowed to be processed when importing nested KML content.

      Setting maxLinkCount = 0 disables this check allowing infinite number of nested content.
      WARNING: If target KML source is deep-nested like a super-overlay then disabling this check should be done with caution.

      Parameters:
      maxLinkCount - Maximum number of NetworkLinks allowed when importing network links. Set maxLinkCount = 0 to disable this check and allow infinite number of nested content.

    • importFromNetworkLinks

      public List<IGISObject> importFromNetworkLinks()
      Recursively imports KML objects from all visited NetworkLinks starting from the base KML document. This must be called after reader is closed otherwise an IllegalArgumentException will be thrown.

      WARNING: Use this method with caution. Loading a KML document that is deeply nested like a super-overlay could load a large number of KML NetworkLinks each with a large number of features. Use setMaxLinkCount(int) to restrict number of nested network links. If limit exceeded then maxLinkCountExceeded will be set to true.

      Returns:
      list of visited networkLink URIs, empty list if no reachable networkLinks are found, never null
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if reader is still open

    • importFromNetworkLinks

      public void importFromNetworkLinks(KmlReader.ImportEventHandler handler)
      Recursively imports KML objects from all visited NetworkLinks starting from the base KML document. Callback is provided to process each feature as the networkLinks are parsed. This must be called after reader is closed otherwise an IllegalArgumentException will be thrown.

      Use setMaxLinkCount(int) to restrict number of nested network links. If limit exceeded then maxLinkCountExceeded will be set to true.

      Parameters:
      handler - ImportEventHandler is called when each new GISObject is encountered during parsing. This cannot be null.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if ImportEventHandler is null or reader is still open when invoked
